WEBVTT

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:04.300
Fuyuhashi!

00:00:04.300 --> 00:00:06.760
You don't want to be a killer, right?

00:00:06.760 --> 00:00:09.080
You want to save people.

00:00:09.080 --> 00:00:11.970
You escaped on your own.

00:00:13.380 --> 00:00:17.780
Were you about to let him escape?

00:00:17.780 --> 00:00:19.220
Hey, wait...

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:23.510
Goroku's orders are absolute.

00:00:27.990 --> 00:00:33.770
[Reboot, Last Day]

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:39.400
Sorry, Fuyuhashi.

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:43.800
I disobeyed Mr. Goroku's orders.

00:00:52.050 --> 00:00:54.220
Before she died...

00:00:55.570 --> 00:00:58.320
Machi said she wanted the strength

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:01.050
to rebuild the world ourselves.

00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:12.220
I'll lend you a hand.

00:01:12.790 --> 00:01:14.420
Fuyuhashi...

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:19.280
Kiriya.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:22.480
We're waging war against Mr. Goroku.

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:26.700
That's what I've been waiting to hear!

00:01:26.700 --> 00:01:28.770
Should we start with this guy?

00:01:28.770 --> 00:01:30.430
Please, spare me.

00:01:30.430 --> 00:01:32.670
I'll do anything you say.

00:01:32.670 --> 00:01:34.550
Mr. Kikuchi.

00:01:34.550 --> 00:01:38.740
I deeply apologize for killing your men.

00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:40.730
What?

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:46.510
I plan to seize the organization from Goroku.

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:49.830
But I can't manage its people alone.

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:53.100
I'd appreciate your assistance.

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:55.760
Do we even stand a chance?

00:01:55.760 --> 00:01:58.860
Doesn't matter, you don't get a say in this.

00:01:58.860 --> 00:02:00.590
Yes, of course.

00:02:10.820 --> 00:02:13.410
Evening, Mr. Kikuchi.

00:02:13.410 --> 00:02:15.150
Is the deed done?

00:02:15.150 --> 00:02:18.790
Kikuchi spilled where the ten billion was.

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:23.380
If you want your money back,
keep your hands off of Natsumi.

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:26.100
Excuse me, gentlemen.

00:02:28.150 --> 00:02:31.010
I take it Fuyuhashi is with you?

00:02:34.750 --> 00:02:37.800
I'm taking the organization for myself, sir.

00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:42.990
I think of you as my own son.

00:02:42.990 --> 00:02:46.030
You were already set to take my place.

00:02:46.030 --> 00:02:48.230
Aim higher, Fuyuhashi.

00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:51.150
It's not too late to come back.

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:53.590
Of course it is.

00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.810
Not like I'd want to return anyway.

00:02:55.810 --> 00:02:57.770
Put Natsumi on the line.

00:02:57.770 --> 00:03:00.020
Or else your money's good as gone.

00:03:06.170 --> 00:03:08.250
Hurry up.

00:03:14.650 --> 00:03:16.240
Hello?

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:20.760
What was the weather like
when Takumi was born?

00:03:22.420 --> 00:03:23.990
It was sunny.

00:03:24.770 --> 00:03:27.770
You opened the window for us,

00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:30.200
and there wasn't a single cloud in the sky.

00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:34.750
Natsumi.

00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:38.730
We're going back to him, together.

00:03:44.180 --> 00:03:46.070
Fine.

00:03:46.070 --> 00:03:48.540
I will trade you the money for her life.

00:03:48.540 --> 00:03:51.010
I'm not offering a negotiation here.

00:03:52.140 --> 00:03:56.140
You'll release Natsumi,
and leave the organization.

00:03:56.140 --> 00:03:58.350
Like I could accept those terms.

00:03:58.350 --> 00:04:00.390
That's an order.

00:04:00.970 --> 00:04:05.980
Don't comply, and this money
will go straight to Mr. Ma.

00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:10.700
I'll tell him all about your plans
with Yaichi Makita.

00:04:12.270 --> 00:04:15.970
He would never believe a fake like you.

00:04:16.510 --> 00:04:20.370
He will, if Kikuchi and I back his claim.

00:04:20.370 --> 00:04:22.270
He'll come for your neck,

00:04:22.270 --> 00:04:25.380
and your family.

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:30.720
Release Natsumi by 6AM
at the location we specify.

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:34.900
Then announce your retirement
from the organization.

00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:37.650
Insolent brat...

00:04:37.650 --> 00:04:42.210
Follow orders to protect the family.

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:49.040
That's the tried and true method, right?

00:04:56.080 --> 00:05:00.030
Tamana. Send some men to guard my home.

00:05:00.030 --> 00:05:02.200
- What?
- Hurry!

00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:03.650
Yes, sir.

00:05:05.340 --> 00:05:07.950
I apologize for the commotion, gentlemen.

00:05:07.950 --> 00:05:09.680
Is something the matter?

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:13.830
Not at all. The deal will proceed as planned.

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:17.180
We're treading dangerous waters as is.

00:05:17.180 --> 00:05:19.320
I'd rather we were informed of any risks.

00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:24.800
Hayase has taken the ten billion yen.

00:05:27.270 --> 00:05:31.510
Worry not, we will secure the money from him.

00:05:31.510 --> 00:05:33.140
How so?

00:05:33.140 --> 00:05:36.560
I will make it happen,
by any means necessary.

00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:40.480
He has you backed to a wall.

00:05:40.480 --> 00:05:43.100
Sir, please.

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:45.600
Not with us here.

00:05:51.790 --> 00:05:54.250
Feel free to keep bluffing.

00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:56.480
I'll have you buried under in no time.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:58.730
You think I'm scared?

00:05:58.730 --> 00:06:01.030
I have my husband now.

00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:06.920
Your place has been secured, sir.

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:08.620
Gather our men.

00:06:08.620 --> 00:06:10.230
We're securing negotiation material.

00:06:10.230 --> 00:06:11.930
[Shelter]

00:06:22.990 --> 00:06:24.090
Get in the car.

00:06:24.090 --> 00:06:26.040
This way, everyone.

00:06:28.540 --> 00:06:29.990
- Climb in.
- Hurry!

00:06:29.990 --> 00:06:31.010
Squeeze up front.

00:06:31.010 --> 00:06:32.250
Sorry, it'll be tight.

00:06:32.250 --> 00:06:34.540
Three of you, come here.

00:06:35.450 --> 00:06:36.970
Take care of them.

00:06:36.970 --> 00:06:38.350
Yeah.

00:06:39.680 --> 00:06:41.600
They stormed the place like we thought.

00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:44.100
Should I go light 'em up?

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:46.650
No, not around Shelter.

00:06:46.650 --> 00:06:49.410
Will the rest of your friends be alright?

00:06:49.410 --> 00:06:51.190
We've already sent out a warning.

00:06:51.190 --> 00:06:53.150
What about your family?

00:06:53.150 --> 00:06:54.620
I can send some people over.

00:06:54.620 --> 00:06:58.560
No need, the police are protecting them.

00:06:58.560 --> 00:06:59.930
No one's here.

00:06:59.930 --> 00:07:01.920
They had a read on us.

00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:04.650
Is that so.

00:07:05.340 --> 00:07:07.180
Then aim for our other option.

00:07:07.180 --> 00:07:08.650
But sir, the risks...

00:07:08.650 --> 00:07:11.220
I don't care. Do it.

00:07:45.350 --> 00:07:47.170
Did you want some cocoa?

00:07:47.170 --> 00:07:49.830
Thanks, but I'll pass.

00:07:56.300 --> 00:08:01.520
I'll take the kids, and leave for a while.

00:08:03.710 --> 00:08:08.740
I promise to protect them with my life.

00:08:35.020 --> 00:08:36.540
Hey there. What's our status?

00:08:36.540 --> 00:08:38.850
We're all clear, sir.

00:08:38.850 --> 00:08:40.720
Is Gido around?

00:08:45.060 --> 00:08:46.510
Hello?

00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:49.900
This is Adachi.
I apologize for visiting so early.

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:51.850
May I have a bit of your time?

00:08:52.430 --> 00:08:55.060
I'm terribly sorry. I only just woke up...

00:08:55.060 --> 00:08:58.460
Ma'am, is Gido there with you?

00:08:59.160 --> 00:09:00.830
He is not.

00:09:00.830 --> 00:09:03.620
Have any other incidents occurred?

00:09:04.280 --> 00:09:05.950
No.

00:09:08.160 --> 00:09:10.560
Where else could Gido be?

00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:12.510
Should we try visiting his place again?

00:09:12.510 --> 00:09:14.670
Yeah, let's do that.

00:09:14.670 --> 00:09:16.900
Why don't we wait for him here?

00:09:18.530 --> 00:09:21.540
Riku Hayase will most certainly return.

00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:23.490
How can you be so sure?

00:09:23.490 --> 00:09:25.370
My detective's hunch says so.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:32.570
Taku!

00:09:32.570 --> 00:09:34.190
Grandma!

00:09:35.150 --> 00:09:37.120
- Taku!
- Grandma!

00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:41.610
Don't make a fuss.

00:09:41.610 --> 00:09:44.290
Try anything, and the kid's dead.

00:10:11.260 --> 00:10:13.250
Where's Natsumi?

00:10:14.070 --> 00:10:16.190
I released her, as promised.

00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:17.940
- What?
- But you see,

00:10:17.940 --> 00:10:20.780
once she saw this,

00:10:20.780 --> 00:10:23.290
she sprinted off in a mad dash.

00:10:27.410 --> 00:10:31.280
I didn't want to get the child involved.

00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:34.530
But emergencies
must be dealt with accordingly.

00:10:34.530 --> 00:10:36.180
How'd you get inside?

00:10:36.180 --> 00:10:39.390
We have an associate within the police.

00:10:39.390 --> 00:10:41.920
He let them in through the second floor.

00:10:41.920 --> 00:10:48.220
We told Natsumi if she made a report,
we'd burn the place down.

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:50.840
Takumi...

00:11:47.410 --> 00:11:52.640
A mother's dedication to her child
is truly admirable.

00:11:52.640 --> 00:11:54.530
Wait.

00:11:56.130 --> 00:11:58.300
What a turn of events, eh?

00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:00.340
Give me the money.

00:12:00.340 --> 00:12:06.160
Heed my orders,
or your family goes up in flames.

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:08.980
His family's not my business.

00:12:09.700 --> 00:12:12.300
- Fuyuhashi...
- Oh?

00:12:13.240 --> 00:12:15.710
Betraying his trust already, I see.

00:12:15.710 --> 00:12:18.130
What will you do, Hayase?

00:12:18.130 --> 00:12:23.340
As is, Fuyuhashi will let your family die.

00:12:27.320 --> 00:12:30.080
Give us a moment to talk.

00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:35.470
Fine. But please keep it short.

00:12:44.980 --> 00:12:47.010
Don't buy his threat.

00:12:47.010 --> 00:12:48.710
Give him the money, and we're dead.

00:12:48.710 --> 00:12:52.380
I know. Give me a moment to think.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.700
Fuyuhashi.

00:12:59.900 --> 00:13:02.190
Keep facing my way.

00:13:11.590 --> 00:13:14.300
Makita, this is Hayase.

00:13:15.660 --> 00:13:18.240
We stole Goroku's ten billion.

00:13:18.240 --> 00:13:20.230
Now that's troubling to hear.

00:13:20.230 --> 00:13:23.340
We need him to hand Yaichi the money
to arrest them both.

00:13:23.340 --> 00:13:24.960
I know.

00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:27.640
We'll return Goroku his money.

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:32.860
But we'll have Yaichi Makita join him.

00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:35.950
That'll be your chance to get them.

00:13:35.950 --> 00:13:38.270
That's quite the reckless plan.

00:13:38.270 --> 00:13:40.430
Would Goroku really oblige?

00:13:40.430 --> 00:13:43.260
He's got my family held hostage.

00:13:43.260 --> 00:13:46.120
I'll make him drag Yaichi to the deal.

00:13:46.120 --> 00:13:47.450
Inspector General Makita.

00:13:47.450 --> 00:13:49.990
You want to catch that whale, right?

00:13:50.740 --> 00:13:52.340
Well, this is your last chance.

00:13:52.340 --> 00:13:54.280
Wager your bets on me.

00:13:56.480 --> 00:13:58.700
When is the deal?

00:13:58.700 --> 00:14:00.960
6PM tonight.

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:03.710
I'll make it happen in Arakawa City.

00:14:03.710 --> 00:14:04.910
Tonight?

00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:07.800
He'll kill my family,
I can't wait any longer.

00:14:11.140 --> 00:14:12.960
Alright.

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:19.820
Can we really trust this Makita?

00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:22.840
We don't have any other choice.

00:14:29.330 --> 00:14:31.460
Fuyuhashi and I came to an agreement.

00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:37.230
You'll get your money tonight.
6PM, Arakawa City.

00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:41.930
Under one condition.

00:14:42.570 --> 00:14:45.990
Yaichi Makita joins us for the deal.

00:14:45.990 --> 00:14:50.340
You wouldn't kill us with him around, no?

00:14:50.340 --> 00:14:52.800
I don't think he'd like to join us.

00:14:52.800 --> 00:14:55.280
Then you'll convince him to.

00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:58.160
Listen up.

00:15:01.420 --> 00:15:05.170
If Yaichi doesn't show, we burn the money.

00:15:08.080 --> 00:15:10.670
We'll compete for the bigger bonfire.

00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:14.250
Try me.

00:15:15.670 --> 00:15:17.230
I'm dead serious.

00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:22.300
I can't agree to anything
knowing I'll only die.

00:15:22.300 --> 00:15:27.120
Refuse our offer,
and Mr. Ma will deal with you.

00:15:36.360 --> 00:15:38.500
Fine.

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:41.430
I will see you both tonight, at 6PM sharp.

00:15:48.070 --> 00:15:49.670
Hello.

00:15:49.670 --> 00:15:52.170
Did you hear of our deal?

00:15:52.170 --> 00:15:55.240
Of course.

00:15:57.150 --> 00:16:01.680
Unfortunately, we will have to oblige.

00:16:01.680 --> 00:16:03.800
I will convince my brother
to join you tonight.

00:16:50.800 --> 00:16:55.810
I was enjoying a nice meal with Hazuki.

00:16:55.810 --> 00:16:57.930
What urgent business did you have?

00:17:01.160 --> 00:17:05.250
The money is to be retrieved
at 6PM tonight.

00:17:05.250 --> 00:17:06.820
I see.

00:17:06.820 --> 00:17:09.720
Mr. Goroku sure is a fast worker.

00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:18.120
He asks you to join him for the deal.

00:17:18.120 --> 00:17:19.350
What?

00:17:19.350 --> 00:17:24.180
Hayase refuses to return the money
if you are not present.

00:17:24.180 --> 00:17:26.160
I can tell he's serious.

00:17:26.760 --> 00:17:29.470
You really will lose the money.

00:17:35.430 --> 00:17:37.410
You said he was a pâtissier?

00:17:38.230 --> 00:17:42.340
To think such an ordinary man
is hindering my ambitions.

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:44.840
I understand I'm asking for much.

00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:47.620
But we are all shouldering a risk.

00:17:47.620 --> 00:17:50.210
- If you could consider...
- Of course I'll go.

00:17:51.050 --> 00:17:53.480
Our citizens are counting on me.

00:17:53.480 --> 00:17:56.400
They hope I'll guide us to greater heights.

00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:58.630
For the sake of this nation,

00:17:59.850 --> 00:18:02.680
I'll do what must be done.

00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:06.270
This could be a trap laid by Hayase.

00:18:06.270 --> 00:18:10.090
I have you, and Goroku as my allies.

00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:15.040
I can't allow one man
to crush the dreams of this country.

00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:17.860
This is Adachi, speaking.

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:20.450
Has anything changed since we last spoke?

00:18:20.450 --> 00:18:23.020
No, not at all.

00:18:23.630 --> 00:18:25.610
Shall I bring you a meal?

00:18:25.610 --> 00:18:28.160
You haven't left the house in over a day.

00:18:28.760 --> 00:18:30.370
We'll manage fine, thank you.

00:18:30.370 --> 00:18:34.540
However, you are scaring my grandchild.

00:18:34.540 --> 00:18:37.670
Could we keep communications to a minimum?

00:18:38.190 --> 00:18:40.780
Understood. Our apologies, ma'am.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:49.010
Didn't she seem a bit frightened?

00:18:49.010 --> 00:18:52.430
Of course she's scared,
her grandson almost got kidnapped.

00:18:52.430 --> 00:18:56.050
Hopefully they're not hiding Hayase in there.

00:18:56.050 --> 00:19:00.060
Hayase doesn't realize we know his identity.

00:19:00.060 --> 00:19:02.550
He has no reason to stay hidden from us.

00:19:16.010 --> 00:19:17.700
How is my grandson?

00:19:21.460 --> 00:19:26.030
Move, and the brat's a goner.

00:19:39.570 --> 00:19:41.460
Mrs. Ryoko.

00:19:42.610 --> 00:19:44.510
Answer in a whisper.

00:19:46.380 --> 00:19:48.970
Where is Takumi?

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:54.280
He's in the room next to the living room.

00:19:57.310 --> 00:19:59.610
Please cut my tape.

00:19:59.610 --> 00:20:01.900
I'll go save him.

00:20:10.910 --> 00:20:13.150
No moving, grannie!

00:20:17.630 --> 00:20:19.960
It's reckless to go alone.

00:20:23.170 --> 00:20:25.530
I'll do what has to be done.

00:20:28.280 --> 00:20:32.960
We mustn't be rash.

00:20:34.090 --> 00:20:37.420
Hayase's are known for their tenacity.

00:20:38.240 --> 00:20:39.710
Still...

00:20:39.710 --> 00:20:41.600
Don't worry.

00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:45.000
Riku will come.

00:20:47.060 --> 00:20:48.890
My son, he...

00:20:50.110 --> 00:20:53.080
He changed his entire face

00:20:53.080 --> 00:20:56.440
so he could survive.

00:20:57.940 --> 00:21:00.610
His determination is admirable.

00:21:04.050 --> 00:21:07.200
I admit, he proved me wrong.

00:21:09.040 --> 00:21:11.580
Your husband...

00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:17.040
is more reliable than I thought.

00:21:24.210 --> 00:21:27.400
I see.

00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:32.380
It really is you.

00:21:32.380 --> 00:21:35.020
Isn't it, Natsumi?

00:21:38.370 --> 00:21:41.510
I had my suspicions

00:21:42.180 --> 00:21:45.990
from the way you watched Takumi.

00:21:47.990 --> 00:21:52.690
Once I realized Riku changed his face,
I knew.

00:21:56.180 --> 00:22:01.620
Of course you would risk everything
for Takumi.

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:08.980
The reason you were pushed down the stairs...

00:22:12.700 --> 00:22:15.660
is all my fault, Mother.

00:22:17.760 --> 00:22:20.310
I'm so, so sorry.

00:22:26.250 --> 00:22:32.600
Then I suppose I'll have you look after me
for years to come.

00:22:38.250 --> 00:22:40.160
Natsumi.

00:22:43.010 --> 00:22:47.890
I'm so thankful you're alive.

00:22:49.430 --> 00:22:51.920
I truly am, dear.

00:22:57.110 --> 00:23:00.460
Gosh, we can't be a crying mess.

00:23:01.200 --> 00:23:05.610
We have to stay strong, and protect Taku.

00:23:08.860 --> 00:23:10.340
Yes.

00:23:11.080 --> 00:23:13.970
I'm sure Riku will come for us, too.

00:23:43.440 --> 00:23:45.060
Stop.

00:23:46.630 --> 00:23:48.190
Let me see the money.

00:23:48.190 --> 00:23:50.740
Where's Yaichi Makita?

00:24:04.770 --> 00:24:08.760
So you must be Hayase.

00:24:10.410 --> 00:24:13.400
What you've stolen is not simply "money".

00:24:14.130 --> 00:24:17.660
Now return to me the future of this nation.

00:24:48.730 --> 00:24:50.550
It's all here, sir.

00:24:51.670 --> 00:24:53.610
Those bills are the real deal.

00:24:54.240 --> 00:24:56.880
Go on, Mr. Yaichi Makita.

00:24:56.880 --> 00:24:58.830
It's all yours.

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:07.740
It seems you're waiting
for the police to step in.

00:25:08.390 --> 00:25:10.150
But that won't be happening.

00:25:11.590 --> 00:25:13.460
No, allow me to rephrase.

00:25:13.460 --> 00:25:14.920
One officer will join us.

00:25:14.920 --> 00:25:18.560
He is my strongest ally.

00:25:19.800 --> 00:25:22.800
Hey there, Inspector Gido.

00:25:24.010 --> 00:25:25.320
Makita...

00:25:25.320 --> 00:25:27.390
Drop the gun.

00:25:27.390 --> 00:25:30.020
Or your family is done for.

00:25:35.170 --> 00:25:36.650
Aoi...

00:25:36.650 --> 00:25:39.170
I'm sorry. We got caught.

00:25:54.090 --> 00:25:57.780
I must commend your efforts, you two.

00:25:57.780 --> 00:26:00.940
Allow me to treat you to one last meal.

00:26:51.930 --> 00:26:53.010
There's an exit out back.

00:27:02.540 --> 00:27:04.960
Kiriya, my place. Hurry!

00:27:08.010 --> 00:27:10.980
Freeze! Police!

00:27:10.980 --> 00:27:12.490
- Freeze!
- Secure him.

00:27:15.690 --> 00:27:17.790
Great work, Hijikata.

00:27:17.790 --> 00:27:19.600
You too, sir.

00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:22.190
We've finally captured our whale.

00:27:22.190 --> 00:27:23.730
That, we have.

00:27:24.500 --> 00:27:25.790
What's going on?

00:27:25.790 --> 00:27:28.710
Simply put, I was your enemy.

00:27:29.600 --> 00:27:35.780
Hayase helped me secure the evidence needed

00:27:35.780 --> 00:27:38.570
to arrest the politician, Yaichi Makita.

00:27:38.570 --> 00:27:40.970
He'll kill my family,
I can't wait any longer.

00:27:40.970 --> 00:27:45.440
Alright. I'll send in
our Second Investigation Team.

00:27:47.650 --> 00:27:53.310
They'll enter with a stun grenade,
so close your eyes on my signal.

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:55.130
Makita, what about my family?

00:27:55.130 --> 00:27:59.230
There's still a spy here.
I'd rather not say much.

00:27:59.230 --> 00:28:01.400
I'll prepare you an escape route.

00:28:01.400 --> 00:28:03.850
Take Goroku, and leave the scene.

00:28:03.850 --> 00:28:05.080
Why did you betray me?

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:07.650
You started this betrayal.

00:28:10.280 --> 00:28:12.420
12 years ago.

00:28:13.130 --> 00:28:15.480
My wife's hit-and-run.

00:28:16.510 --> 00:28:19.260
The one truly in the driver's seat

00:28:20.280 --> 00:28:22.190
was you, was it not?

00:28:24.610 --> 00:28:28.550
My wife chose to take the blame for you,

00:28:31.190 --> 00:28:33.740
knowing it would affect my career.

00:28:35.470 --> 00:28:40.020
Her love for you triumphed
anything she felt for me.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:46.510
I know your relationship
continues to this day.

00:28:52.330 --> 00:28:53.750
Still,

00:28:55.790 --> 00:28:58.420
an affair is no crime.

00:28:59.730 --> 00:29:01.810
It's not punishable by the law.

00:29:03.800 --> 00:29:06.060
So I spent my sweet time,

00:29:07.230 --> 00:29:10.850
carefully waiting for this day to come.

00:29:12.010 --> 00:29:13.760
You...

00:29:22.580 --> 00:29:24.170
My dear brother.

00:29:27.460 --> 00:29:30.300
I've always despised you.

00:29:37.120 --> 00:29:39.060
Yaichi Makita.

00:29:40.690 --> 00:29:45.720
You are under arrest for engaging in bribery.

00:29:47.790 --> 00:29:49.970
What an absurd revenge scheme.

00:29:51.960 --> 00:29:54.280
My career is far from over.

00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:57.800
I won't let it end here.

00:29:59.190 --> 00:30:05.430
Japan needs Yaichi Makita for its future.

00:30:28.670 --> 00:30:31.940
Call your men, and have them free my family.

00:30:32.720 --> 00:30:34.430
Hurry.

00:30:34.430 --> 00:30:36.160
I don't know their number.

00:30:36.160 --> 00:30:38.750
Tamana hired them.

00:30:39.410 --> 00:30:41.190
Kiriya, gun it.

00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:43.650
You're too late.

00:30:43.650 --> 00:30:48.980
They're to burn the place down at 6:05PM.

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:07.910
- Hello?
- Adachi! Where are you?

00:31:07.910 --> 00:31:09.600
In front of Hayase Patisserie.

00:31:09.600 --> 00:31:11.590
- Barge in, now!
- What?

00:31:11.590 --> 00:31:14.420
They're gonna kill my family! Hurry!

00:31:15.270 --> 00:31:18.020
You're trusting a criminal?

00:31:19.470 --> 00:31:21.230
- Alright.
- Ready?

00:31:21.230 --> 00:31:23.290
Please, let my grandson go!

00:31:23.290 --> 00:31:24.970
Shut it, grannie.

00:31:24.970 --> 00:31:26.660
Mother!

00:31:34.910 --> 00:31:37.140
There's one in the kitchen!

00:31:44.880 --> 00:31:47.430
Bitch!

00:31:58.670 --> 00:31:59.930
Yikes.

00:31:59.930 --> 00:32:02.320
Teramoto, call for back up.

00:32:16.580 --> 00:32:20.160
Sorry, orders are orders.

00:32:20.160 --> 00:32:22.030
I can't believe it.

00:32:22.910 --> 00:32:25.480
You really were the spy.

00:32:25.480 --> 00:32:27.420
Why are you helping Goroku?

00:32:27.420 --> 00:32:30.090
What? I'm just doing a part-time gig.

00:32:31.420 --> 00:32:34.680
Blame my gambling addiction for that.

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:37.610
Anyway, these jobs were texted to me.

00:32:37.610 --> 00:32:40.710
I've got no idea who the client is.

00:32:59.460 --> 00:33:01.220
Riku!

00:33:09.500 --> 00:33:11.100
Let go!

00:33:22.120 --> 00:33:24.140
You're a fake after all!

00:33:25.790 --> 00:33:28.470
Then what does that make you, Teramoto?

00:33:28.470 --> 00:33:29.510
What?

00:33:29.510 --> 00:33:34.200
You're worse than a fake, you traitor!

00:34:23.300 --> 00:34:25.350
Sir!

00:34:25.350 --> 00:34:28.050
Adachi. Deal with him.

00:34:28.050 --> 00:34:29.470
Right.

00:34:34.120 --> 00:34:36.400
Riku! Takumi!

00:34:36.400 --> 00:34:38.410
- Takumi is...
- Takumi?

00:34:38.410 --> 00:34:39.980
Takumi!

00:34:43.630 --> 00:34:45.280
Takumi.

00:34:45.280 --> 00:34:47.080
You alright, Takumi?

00:34:48.330 --> 00:34:49.820
Takumi!

00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:55.480
Takumi?

00:34:58.880 --> 00:35:00.830
You're alright, bud.

00:35:24.050 --> 00:35:25.520
- Nothing hurts?
- No.

00:35:25.520 --> 00:35:27.970
Then we'll check your eyes, next.

00:35:27.970 --> 00:35:30.020
Please tell me if you feel any pain.

00:35:47.320 --> 00:35:50.460
I worked as Goroku's treasurer.

00:35:50.460 --> 00:35:52.900
I know everything about this incident.

00:35:52.900 --> 00:35:56.200
I will confess all of my wrongdoings.

00:36:19.370 --> 00:36:21.700
Are you Riku Hayase?

00:36:21.700 --> 00:36:23.100
Yes, sir.

00:36:23.960 --> 00:36:26.370
I am Riku Hayase.

00:36:39.790 --> 00:36:42.470
- Dad!
- Taku...

00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:49.430
Don't worry, kiddo. I'll be back.

00:36:49.430 --> 00:36:53.220
Let's make a Hayase Shortcake
when I'm home, alright?

00:37:02.740 --> 00:37:04.570
Chief Mikami, I must ask a favor.

00:37:04.570 --> 00:37:06.090
Quiet.

00:37:06.090 --> 00:37:08.480
Please, let her meet her sister.

00:37:08.480 --> 00:37:10.910
Her sister doesn't have long to live.

00:37:10.910 --> 00:37:13.140
- Sir, please.
- Enough!

00:37:13.140 --> 00:37:15.380
You damn fake.

00:37:16.140 --> 00:37:17.820
Ms. Adachi, please.

00:37:17.820 --> 00:37:20.300
She did all this for her sister's sake.

00:37:20.300 --> 00:37:23.050
Her sister is hospitalized
at Meikan University Hospital.

00:37:23.050 --> 00:37:27.120
Please, at least let her say goodbye.

00:37:27.120 --> 00:37:29.000
Don't dawdle.

00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:32.590
- Adachi, please!
- Move it, Hayase!

00:37:36.220 --> 00:37:37.580
Get in.

00:37:58.850 --> 00:38:03.380
I received an order from Chief Mikami.

00:38:03.380 --> 00:38:06.680
He asks that we stop by
Meikan University Hospital.

00:38:06.680 --> 00:38:10.460
You don't need to lie.
I'm already headed there.

00:38:11.370 --> 00:38:13.000
You're...

00:38:13.860 --> 00:38:16.550
My boss's orders.

00:39:24.410 --> 00:39:27.240
You surprised me.

00:39:31.260 --> 00:39:32.930
Ayaka.

00:39:34.610 --> 00:39:37.580
I won't be able to see you for a while.

00:39:39.520 --> 00:39:44.970
A laywer will come to visit you.
Listen to what they say, okay?

00:39:47.730 --> 00:39:49.440
I...

00:39:53.560 --> 00:39:55.490
I will always love you.

00:40:04.630 --> 00:40:07.020
You don't have to lie anymore.

00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:14.130
Did you think I wouldn't catch on?

00:40:15.150 --> 00:40:18.150
I know you aren't my sister.

00:40:20.970 --> 00:40:23.190
But I couldn't say anything.

00:40:25.950 --> 00:40:30.460
You were practically my lifeline.

00:40:31.360 --> 00:40:33.930
I was scared you would leave me, too.

00:40:40.190 --> 00:40:43.830
My sister was tired of caring for me.

00:40:43.830 --> 00:40:45.920
She left me, didn't she?

00:40:45.920 --> 00:40:47.560
She must have hired you to...

00:40:47.560 --> 00:40:49.360
No.

00:40:49.360 --> 00:40:51.880
No, no.

00:40:52.710 --> 00:40:59.040
Your sister treasured you with all her heart.

00:41:00.720 --> 00:41:04.020
Ichika wanted to save you.

00:41:04.020 --> 00:41:07.980
She put her life on the line, all for you.

00:41:11.030 --> 00:41:16.160
So promise me this. You have to live.

00:41:16.980 --> 00:41:18.770
You have to.

00:41:20.080 --> 00:41:23.070
You can't ever give up, okay?

00:41:34.840 --> 00:41:36.680
Ichika.

00:41:41.030 --> 00:41:43.400
Thank you for staying with me.

00:41:50.310 --> 00:41:53.140
I'm the one who's grateful, Ayaka.

00:41:54.650 --> 00:41:57.720
I lost my entire family.

00:41:58.570 --> 00:42:01.350
But you were my ray of light in the dark.

00:42:03.930 --> 00:42:05.650
Thank you.

00:42:43.960 --> 00:42:46.060
I'll focus my efforts on Shelter.

00:42:46.060 --> 00:42:48.640
Kikuchi will lead the organization.

00:42:48.640 --> 00:42:50.850
Fuyuhashi is only using you,

00:42:50.850 --> 00:42:53.050
Kikuchi.

00:42:53.050 --> 00:42:55.610
Now, now. No need to be a sore loser.

00:42:55.610 --> 00:42:58.610
Have one more delicious meal for the road.

00:42:58.610 --> 00:43:00.680
Courtesy of me, of course.

00:43:03.780 --> 00:43:06.700
Money is an infinite resource.

00:43:08.110 --> 00:43:11.200
It has become nothing more than a symbol.

00:43:11.200 --> 00:43:13.050
It's practically worthless as is.

00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:17.200
What matters more, is how you use it.

00:43:17.200 --> 00:43:21.360
I wanted to use money to change this country.

00:43:22.140 --> 00:43:24.650
To change our future.

00:43:26.240 --> 00:43:28.540
Think of it as a revolution of sorts.

00:43:28.540 --> 00:43:30.250
Fuyuhashi.

00:43:31.590 --> 00:43:36.970
What will you use this organization for?

00:43:38.920 --> 00:43:42.590
I'll use it to save homeless kids in need.

00:43:43.460 --> 00:43:45.440
You're thinking too small.

00:43:45.440 --> 00:43:48.400
You won't change a thing.

00:43:48.400 --> 00:43:50.150
I will.

00:43:51.380 --> 00:43:54.250
Now I understand.

00:43:54.250 --> 00:44:00.190
You can talk big, and let money
and politics rule you all you want.

00:44:00.190 --> 00:44:04.460
But those desperate to protect
their immediate family are way stronger.

00:44:07.310 --> 00:44:10.670
I'll find more of my family out there,

00:44:11.800 --> 00:44:14.200
and change this world for the better.

00:44:19.530 --> 00:44:23.250
Eat up while it's hot.

00:44:40.190 --> 00:44:42.780
Start by improving your cooking skills.

00:44:44.980 --> 00:44:47.080
Thank you, sir.

00:45:14.780 --> 00:45:16.620
Fuyuhashi!

00:45:16.620 --> 00:45:19.630
- You bastard!
- Eisuke Kikuchi.

00:45:19.630 --> 00:45:24.090
You're under arrest for your involvement
in organized crime.

00:45:27.280 --> 00:45:29.100
No, I...

00:45:58.970 --> 00:46:02.160
To stick the nail in Yaichi Makita's coffin,

00:46:03.010 --> 00:46:05.720
we require your testimony.

00:46:09.490 --> 00:46:16.050
If I don't cooperate,
Yaichi Makita will slip through your fingers.

00:46:17.170 --> 00:46:21.870
His survival could allow me
to return to the limelight.

00:46:24.270 --> 00:46:28.970
If you choose to assist us
by confessing to your crimes,

00:46:29.910 --> 00:46:34.880
we will drive off the Hong Kong organization.

00:46:34.880 --> 00:46:36.460
Meaning?

00:46:37.290 --> 00:46:40.680
The Japanese police will pressure them

00:46:40.680 --> 00:46:42.840
into leaving your family alone.

00:46:42.840 --> 00:46:44.590
This is the only way

00:46:45.570 --> 00:46:48.470
you can guarantee your family's safety.

00:46:51.280 --> 00:46:54.810
Survive to revolutionize this country,

00:46:55.920 --> 00:46:58.900
or accept the punishment awaiting you,

00:47:00.700 --> 00:47:03.200
and save your family.

00:47:04.830 --> 00:47:07.050
The choice is yours.

00:47:12.520 --> 00:47:13.960
My family.

00:47:15.360 --> 00:47:18.420
Please, save my family.

00:47:31.290 --> 00:47:34.950
That should be enough pancakes for everyone.

00:47:34.950 --> 00:47:37.280
You made way too many.

00:47:38.380 --> 00:47:43.230
Kiriya. Do I suck at cooking?

00:47:46.740 --> 00:47:48.570
Yeah, you do.

00:47:49.360 --> 00:47:50.480
Shut up.

00:47:50.480 --> 00:47:53.230
Then don't ask.

00:48:01.320 --> 00:48:03.430
I leave them to you, Kiriya.

00:48:04.010 --> 00:48:05.970
What're you talking about?

00:48:07.020 --> 00:48:09.040
I'll be caught soon enough.

00:48:09.040 --> 00:48:13.650
I'll say I did all the dirty work.

00:48:14.330 --> 00:48:19.100
You might face a couple years, too.

00:48:19.100 --> 00:48:20.970
But after you're out...

00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:24.900
protect Shelter with Aoi.

00:48:24.900 --> 00:48:29.840
I'll turn myself in,
and say I was behind everything.

00:48:29.840 --> 00:48:33.180
Why do you think I stuck by your side?

00:48:33.180 --> 00:48:34.970
Don't you dare.

00:48:39.150 --> 00:48:43.020
If I hadn't met you, I'd be long dead.

00:48:44.060 --> 00:48:47.380
You saved us all.

00:48:48.070 --> 00:48:51.620
Who else would we save, but you?

00:48:53.620 --> 00:48:57.360
Please grant Machi's dream for us.

00:49:00.880 --> 00:49:03.410
Kiriya, I can't run forever.

00:49:04.160 --> 00:49:06.110
Yes, you can.

00:49:06.110 --> 00:49:09.990
Use that method.

00:49:12.050 --> 00:49:13.650
The Kaisei Party
[3 weeks later]

00:49:13.650 --> 00:49:18.090
has withdrawn from elections.
[3 weeks later]

00:49:18.090 --> 00:49:20.910
Yaichi Makita, the Kaisei Party candidate,

00:49:20.910 --> 00:49:25.420
was arrested for using illegal capital

00:49:25.420 --> 00:49:28.090
to fund his campaign and career.
[Yaichi Makita steps down as candidate]

00:49:28.090 --> 00:49:31.080
- See you later.
- Careful now.

00:49:31.080 --> 00:49:33.950
I'll be late tonight, so reheat dinner, okay?

00:49:33.950 --> 00:49:36.640
- Okay!
- Take care, dear.

00:49:59.160 --> 00:50:02.180
[Divorce Forms]

00:50:05.910 --> 00:50:11.200
I'll be transferred to Niigata next month.

00:50:11.200 --> 00:50:16.600
I suppose our current administration
put in a word for me.

00:50:19.190 --> 00:50:22.840
Despite everything, life goes on.

00:50:22.840 --> 00:50:27.570
Money and politics still rule the world.

00:50:28.480 --> 00:50:31.080
Why are you telling me all this?

00:50:39.430 --> 00:50:43.290
I suppose I'm just airing out my losses.

00:50:46.390 --> 00:50:49.080
I wanted to prove to the world

00:50:51.950 --> 00:50:58.600
that there was more to life
than making your family happy.

00:51:01.900 --> 00:51:06.810
I wonder what it truly means to be happy?

00:51:12.900 --> 00:51:16.370
Dessert always puts a smile on a face.

00:51:17.440 --> 00:51:20.240
Stop by for a slice of cake sometime.

00:51:27.390 --> 00:51:29.200
If I ever feel up to it.

00:51:31.340 --> 00:51:33.020
Well then.

00:51:41.380 --> 00:51:45.160
Thank you for your cooperation.

00:51:46.200 --> 00:51:49.260
Riku Hayase.

00:52:02.620 --> 00:52:04.740
[Live: The Police Replacement Incident]

00:52:04.740 --> 00:52:08.400
The innocent Riku Hayase,
now with a changed face,

00:52:08.400 --> 00:52:10.460
has just returned home.

00:52:10.460 --> 00:52:12.890
Reporters are absolutely crowding him.

00:52:12.890 --> 00:52:15.200
Though he will be on house arrest,

00:52:15.200 --> 00:52:17.520
many citizens are pleading
for his penalty to be reduced.

00:52:17.520 --> 00:52:21.720
Judges will make their final decision
in the coming days.

00:52:51.150 --> 00:52:54.690
Thanks for holding up the fort, Takumi.

00:53:03.280 --> 00:53:05.070
I'm home.

00:53:19.680 --> 00:53:22.120
Your dad's finally home.

00:53:41.410 --> 00:53:43.050
Welcome home.

00:53:44.520 --> 00:53:46.180
I'm back.

00:54:08.130 --> 00:54:11.960
This is what he left behind for you.

00:54:17.830 --> 00:54:24.140
We also found your husband
had rented a safe in Chiba.

00:54:24.140 --> 00:54:29.200
Within it, was 52 million yen in cash.

00:54:30.910 --> 00:54:33.040
That money...

00:54:34.160 --> 00:54:37.390
It couldn't have come from legal sources.

00:54:38.270 --> 00:54:40.500
We have no way of knowing.

00:54:40.500 --> 00:54:43.640
Either way, it is your inheritance.

00:54:43.640 --> 00:54:48.430
Then please, give that money to the Hayase's.

00:54:48.430 --> 00:54:51.960
They have suffered the most.

00:54:53.780 --> 00:55:00.050
Truth be told, Natsumi Hayase's lawyer
hoped to see you for this very reason.

00:55:02.030 --> 00:55:05.500
Who donated the 52 million yen?

00:55:05.500 --> 00:55:07.570
They wish to remain anonymous.

00:55:07.570 --> 00:55:11.970
For now, let's focus on your own recovery.

00:55:12.600 --> 00:55:14.020
Right.

00:55:18.300 --> 00:55:20.660
I have a favor to ask of you, Mr. Kaieda.

00:55:20.660 --> 00:55:22.740
Another one?

00:55:22.740 --> 00:55:27.610
If something ever happens to me,
please save my sister, Ayaka.

00:55:36.770 --> 00:55:42.410
[Riku Hayase, 3 years detention]
[5 years suspended sentence]

00:55:43.350 --> 00:55:49.810
[5 years, 8 months later]

00:55:55.260 --> 00:55:57.150
Thank you.

00:56:10.630 --> 00:56:13.160
Natsumi Hayase?

00:56:16.380 --> 00:56:17.910
Who are you?

00:56:23.220 --> 00:56:26.470
I'm Machimura, from the NPO known as Shelter.

00:56:26.470 --> 00:56:28.450
I've come to get you.

00:56:31.540 --> 00:56:33.370
I've heard the rumors.

00:56:33.370 --> 00:56:36.760
You refused your family's visitations.

00:56:36.760 --> 00:56:40.890
I guess you'd only trouble them,
being a criminal and all.

00:56:44.710 --> 00:56:47.970
Would you like to come help out at Shelter?

00:56:47.970 --> 00:56:50.840
You might find a new family there.

00:56:53.960 --> 00:56:58.400
If you're so lost, why not just hop in?

00:57:14.520 --> 00:57:16.580
Hey, wait.

00:57:21.310 --> 00:57:24.510
This is your home.

00:57:24.510 --> 00:57:26.760
That's none of your business.

00:57:34.120 --> 00:57:35.810
You forgot this.

